Now, zip is introduced but heroku fails with Error R14 (Memory quota exceeded).
Even with two forks...
Use radis-sever externally?
=> NO. Redis is an alternative to S3, not Heroku server

One solution below.

===========
=   S3    =
===========
   ^ |
   | V
=========== 
= Browser = 
=========== 
   ^ |
   | V
===========
= Heroku  =
===========

When submitting xml file
  Compress xml to zip
  Make json files
  Send zip to S3
  Send json to S3

When accessing web page
  Download html/css/js
  Get json from S3
  Render pages
